race.comment: MALBEC MAN (1) is unlucky to still be a maiden placing in all five starts to date and strikes a very winnable contest here. Gets a stack of weight off with the 3kg claim and should be right there when the judge calls a halt. Former NSW galloper BETTER BREAKOUT (3) hit the frame in his first outing for the new stable and will have come on with that run now under the belt. Expected to feature prominently. RED CITY SUN (7) may have suffered from the dreaded second-up syndrome last time out but go on the solid second here when resuming. Worth another chance from the inside alley. CHANCE (4) has hit the top-five in all six career efforts and looks a must for the exotics players. SMOKIN REELS (2) best of the rest on debut.
